data.text:
She was born in England in 1924. At a very young age Mary was very interested in mathematics. Math was her favourite subject at school. When she grew up, she entered Birmingham University to devote herself to science. She was very smart and got a job in a company which developed commercial computers.

Together with her husband, she worked with computers for a long time and was a pioneering programmer and computer scientist. He had a son who later became the Internet discoverer.

Nowadays, you cannot imagine life without the Internet, and any news in technological sphere is connected in this or that way with the world wide web.
